ctions (unspecified)", "work": "Selections (unspecified)", "composer": null, "performers": []}, {"label": "Selections (unspecified)", "work": "Selections (unspecified)", "composer": null, "performers": [{"id": "58901", "name": "Clifton Fadiman", "qid": null, "roles": ["host"]}]}], "quotes": [{"speaker": "Bill Coleman", "qid": "Q358891", "text": "World war number two had been going on for nearly two years in America. The trio was beginning to become popular, and we co-starred with Hazel Scott after her return from Hollywood for a benefit to buy watches for the Soviet Army, which had taken place at Carnegie Hall the 11th of April, 1943. The trio did a few numbers and for the finale, we were joined by a trombonist named Frank Orchard, and the trumpetist Jack Butler.", "caption": "1943 benefit concert with Hazel Scott and Frank Orchard", "conf": "high", "first_person": null, "doc_title": "71542_Bill Coleman autobiographical manuscript", "collection": "rutgers", "url": "https://rucore.libraries.rutgers.edu/rutgers-lib/71542/"}], "featured_people": [{"qid": "Q329849", "id": "53562", "name": "Adolph Green"}, {"qid": "Q2623674", "id": "18459", "name": "Al Hall"}, {"qid": "Q731178", "id": "4712", "name": "Albert Ammons"}, {"qid": "Q352013", "id": "9795", "name": "Benny Morton"}, {"qid": "Q175078", "id": "53561", "name": "Betty Comden"}, {"qid": "Q358891", "id": "60285", "name": "Bill Coleman"}, {"qid": "Q713276", "id": "23154", "name": "Edmond Hall"}, {"qid": "Q488340", "id": "3289", "name": "Ellis Larkins"}, {"qid": "Q3048518", "id": "58702", "name": "Georgia Gibbs"}, {"qid": "Q431656", "id": "36708", "name": "Hazel Scott"}, {"qid": "Q97291", "id": "39711", "name": "Kenneth Spencer"}, {"qid": "Q84436882", "id": "58703", "name": "Paul Baron"}, {"qid": "Q1399599", "id": "43342", "name": "Pete Johnson"}, {"qid": "Q720654", "id": "54607", "name": "Sid Catlett"}, {"qid": "Q506052", "id": "1195", "name": "Teddy Wilson"}]}